uot;&gt;&gt; Speaking of Karma, everything has a karma of it&#39;s own. Tantra,=\r\n as it stands today, is roughly divided into two major geographic and philo=\r\nsophical demarcations. The style practiced in South India - mostly Dakshina=\r\n Margi - and that practiced in Bengal and adjacent areas - mostly Vama Marg=\r\ni. In my personal opinion, the adherents of the path in both cases, general=\r\nly speaking, have been trapped in two delusions born out of collateral bypr=\r\noducts of their respective paths. The first step of Shakti sadhana is gener=\r\nating shakti. Second step is holding the shakti. Third step is channeling t=\r\nhe shakti. In view of this, one school of Tantra that is prevalent today ha=\r\ns tied itself up in too much of technicalities, such that on an average the=\r\ny forget to capture shakti (here shakti means energy, not Shakti the suprem=\r\ne Goddess). WHile the other school is able to generate and hold shakti much=\r\n better, only to commercialize the same and/or misuse it (generally=A0 spea=\r\nking, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Ve=\r\nrdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&gt;=A0 expcetions are there too). End result, both event=\r\nually do not end up producing enough genuine Tantrik saints. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;=\r\ndiv align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&gt;=\r\n &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana=\r\n&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;=\r\n#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&gt; i am wondering &quot;if at all&qu=\r\not; and &quot;what kind&quot; of karmic liabilities one might be getting in=\r\nto ?&gt;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div align=